SHENZHEN , July 29 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- More than 110 photos depicting the Hong Kong -stationed Chinese troops ' entry and taking over of Hong Kong defense duties are on exhibition in Shenzhen .
The show , which formally opened to the public today in the Shenzhen Museum , is to celebrate the stationing of the Chinese People 's Liberation Army -LRB- PLA -RRB- troops in Hong Kong as well as to mark the 70th anniversary of the founding of the PLA. Wang Yufa , deputy commissar of the PLA troops in Hong Kong , pledged at the opening ceremony of the exhibition that the troops will work hard to help maintain the stability and prosperity of Hong Kong and to contribute to the reunification of the motherland .
Bai Tian , a member of the standing committee of the Shenzhen City 's Communist Party Committee , also spoke at the ceremony .
